<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 04 at 3:38PM EDT until August 04 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 415 PM EDT
FOR EAST CENTRAL CENTRE...NORTH CENTRAL JUNIATA...NORTHEASTERN
MIFFLIN...WESTERN SNYDER AND SOUTHWESTERN UNION COUNTIES...
At 337 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Weikert, moving
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Woodward, Mcalisterville, McClure, Millheim, Beaver Springs,
Aaronsburg, Richfield, Rebersburg, Mount Pleasant Mills, Paxtonville,
Coburn and Troxelville.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
